{
  "text": "Regardless of the motives for launching a new venture, starting and succeeding at your own business is a very risky undertaking. A 2002 Small Business Administration study found that approximately two-thirds of new firms are still operating after two years, but only approximately 40% of these businesses make it to their sixth year of operation. Yet, success is possible, as evidenced by well-known success stories such as Yahoo and Hotmail, both founded by immigrants [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
